9-Gregorio-V.jpg|thumb|right|An [[early Christian sarcophagi|early Christian sarcophagus]] in which Pope Gregory V was buried after his tomb was discovered beneath the pavement during the demolition|alt=A photo of an early Christian sarcophagus]]\n[[File:Tomb of Pope Adrian IV.jpg|thumb|right|The sarcophagus of Pope Adrian IV, which is extant in the Vatican Grottoes|alt=A photo of the sarcophagus of Pope Adrian IV]]\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Tomb of Pope Nicholas III.jpg|thumb|right|After the destruction of his tomb, Nicholas III was combined with two of his relatives.|alt=A photo of the combined tomb of Pope Nicholas III]] -->\n[[File:Giacomo Grimaldi 004.jpg|thumb|right|Drawing of the tomb of Boniface VIII together with a shrine to Boniface IV]]\n[[File:Tomb of Boniface VIII.jpg|thumb|right|The extant sarcophagus of Boniface VIII|alt=A photo of the sarcophagus of Pope Boniface VIII]]\n[[File:Tomb of pope Urbanus VI.jpg|thumb|right|The nearly dumped sarcophagus of Urban VI|alt=A photo of the sarcophagus of Pope Urban VI]]\n[[File:Tomb of Pope Innocent VII.jpg|thumb|right|The remains of Pope Innocent VII were translated to a copy of the original sarcophagus.|alt=A photo of the sarcophagus of Pope Innocent VII]]\n[[File:Tomb of Pope Nicholas V.jpg|thumb|right|The sarcophagus of Pope Nicholas V|alt=A photo of the sarcophagus of Pope Nicholas V]]\n[[File:Tomb of pope Paulus II.jpg|thumb|right|The sarcophagus of Pope Paul II|alt=A photo of the sarcophagus of Pope Paul II]]\n[[File:Tomb of Sixtus IV Color.jpg|thumb|right|The remains of Pope Sixtus IV were combined with those of Pope Julius II.|alt=A photo of the combined tomb of Popes Sixtus IV and Julius II]]\n[[File:Monument to Innocentius VIII in Saint Peter's Basilica.jpg|thumb|right|The tomb of Pope Innocent VIII was the first to depict a live pontiff.|alt=A photo of the tomb of Pope Innocent VIII]]\n[[File:Tomb of pope Pius III.jpg|thumb|right|The tomb of Pope Pius III was translated to [[Sant'Andrea dell