int Gelasius</small>\n|Tomb located in portico<ref name=\"rear42\">Reardon, 2004, p. 42.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n!scope=row |496\u2013498\n| [[File:Anastasius II.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Anastasius II|Anastasius II]]'''\n|Tomb located in atrium. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear42\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n!scope=row |498\u2013514\n| [[File:Pope Symmachus - Apse mosaic - Sant'Agnese fuori le mura - Rome 2016.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Symmachus|Symmachus]]'''<br /><small>Saint Symmachus</small>\n|Tomb located in portico. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear42\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n!scope=row !scope=row|{{anchor|500\u2013600}}514\u2013523\n|\n| '''[[Pope Hormisdas|Hormisdas]]'''<br /><small>Saint Hormisdas</small>\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear42\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|523\u2013526\n| [[File:Papa Ioannes I.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope John I|John I]]'''<br /><small>Saint John</small>\n|Located in the nave. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear43\">Reardon, 2004, p. 43.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|526\u2013530\n| [[File:Mosaic of Felix IV (III) in Santi Cosma e Damiano, Rome, Italy (527\u2013530).jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Felix IV|Felix IV]]'''<br /><small>Saint Felix</small>\n|Located in the atrium. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear43\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|530\u2013532\n| [[File:Boniface II.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Boniface II|Boniface II]]'''\n|Located in the portico. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear43\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|533\u2013535\n| [[File:Johannes II.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope John II|John II]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear44\">Reardon, 2004, p. 44.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|535\u2013536\n| [[File:Agapitus I.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Agapetus I|Agapetus I]]'''<br /><small>Agapitus<br />Saint Agapetus</small>\n|Located in the atrium. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear44\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|556\u2013561\n| <small>[[File:Pope Pelagius I.jpg