 Leo III|Leo III]]'''<br /><small>Saint Leo</small>\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"|Located in the Chapel of the Madonna of Partorienti. Originally buried in Old Saint Peter's ''(above)''; combined with Leo II and IV by Pope Paschal II; combined sarcophagus destroyed during the demolition; combined with Leo I in 1601 and placed in a sarcophagus under the altar of our Savior della Colonna in new Saint Peter's ''(below)''<ref name=\"rear61\">Reardon, 2004, p. 61.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|{{anchor|800\u2013900}}816\u2013817\n| [[File:Stephen IV.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Stephen IV|Stephen IV]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear61\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|824\u2013827\n| [[File:Eugene II.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Eugene II|Eugene II]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear62\">Reardon, 2004, p. 62.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|827\u2013827\n| [[File:Valentine.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Valentine|Valentine]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear62\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|827\u2013844\n| [[File:Gregory-IV Raban-Maur.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Gregory IV|Gregory IV]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear62\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|844\u2013847\n|\n| '''[[Pope Sergius II|Sergius II]]'''\n|Located in the Altar of the chapel of Saints Sixtus and Fabian. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear62\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"|847\u2013855\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| [[File:Pope St. Leo IV.jpg|70px]]\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| '''[[Pope Leo IV|Leo IV]]''', '''[[Order of Saint Benedict|O.S.B.]]'''<br /><small>Saint Leo</small>\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"|Located under the altar of Our Savior della Colonna. Combined with Leos I, II, and III.<ref name=\"rear62\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|855\u2013858\n|\n| '''[[Pope Benedict III|Benedict III]]'''\n|Located in the Narthex. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear64\">Reardon, 2004, p. 64.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| style=