bined with Leo I in the early seventeenth century; for centuries believed to be under the altar of the Church of San Stefano in Ferrara; combined remains of Leo's I, II, and IV in Chapel of the Madonna of Partorienti when found during the demolition<ref name=\"rear5455\">Reardon, 2004, pp. 54\u201355.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|684\u2013685\n| [[File:BenedictII.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Benedict II|Benedict II]]'''<br /><small>Saint Benedict</small>\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear55\">Reardon, 2004, p. 55.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|685\u2013686\n| [[File:Johannes V.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope John V|John V]]'''\n|Located in the atrium. Destroyed in a [[Arab raid against Rome|Saracen raid in 846]].<ref name=\"rear5556\">Reardon, 2004, pp. 55\u201356.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|686\u2013687\n| [[File:Konon.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Conon|Conon]]'''\n|Located in the left nave. Destroyed during the demolition.<ref name=\"rear56\">Reardon, 2004, p. 56.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|687\u2013701\n| [[File:Sergius I.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Sergius I|Sergius I]]'''<br /><small>Saint Sergius</small>\n|First pope buried in Saint Peter's proper (''not'' a portico); tomb destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear56\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|{{anchor|700\u2013800}}701\u2013705\n| [[File:John VI.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope John VI|John VI]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear57\">Reardon, 2004, p. 57.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"|705\u2013707\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| [[File:Byzantinischer Mosaizist um 705 002.jpg|70px]]\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| '''[[Pope John VII|John VII]]'''\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"|Located in the Chapel of the Blessed Virgin Mary. Destroyed during the demolition; surviving mosaic of John VII in the Vatican grottoes believed to be part of his original tomb<ref name=\"rear57\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|708-708\n| [[File:Sisinnius.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Sisinnius|Sisinnius]]'''\n|Locate