/fifth century sarcophagus]]<ref name=\"rear76\">Reardon, 2004, p. 76.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|{{anchor|1000\u20131100}}1012\u20131024\n| [[File:B Benedikt VIII.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Benedict VIII|Benedict VIII]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear81\">Reardon, 2004, p. 81.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|1024\u20131032\n| [[File:B Johannes XIX.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope John XIX|John XIX]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear81\"/>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|1045\u20131046\n| [[File:B Gregor VI.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Gregory VI|Gregory VI]]'''\n|Destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear82\">Reardon, 2004, p. 82.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| 1049\u20131054\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| [[File:Leon IX.jpg|70px]]\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| '''[[Pope Leo IX|Leo IX]]'''<br /><small>Saint Leo</small>\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"|Originally buried in the east wall of Old Saint Peter's, close to the altar of Gregory I; coffin opened on January 11, 1606 during the demolition and parts were taken as relics; remainder reburied under the altar of Saints Marziale and Valeria,<ref>Reardon, 2004, p. 84.</ref> now dedicated to the stigmata of St. Francis of Assisi<ref>Mann, 2003, p. 27.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|1088\u20131099\n| [[File:BlUrban II.png|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Urban II|Urban II]]''', '''''[[Order of Saint Benedict|O.S.B.]]'''''<br /><small>Blessed Urban</small>\n|First tomb destroyed during the demolition<ref name=\"rear88\">Reardon, 2004, p. 88.</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|{{anchor|1100\u20131200}}1145\u20131153\n| [[File:B Eugen III.jpg|70px]]\n| '''[[Pope Eugene III|Eugene III]]''', '''''[[Cistercians|O.Cist.]]'''''<br /><small>Blessed Eugene</small>\n|Destroyed during the demolition\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| 1154\u20131159\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| [[File:Pope Hadrian IV.jpg|70px]]\n| style=\"background:#c9c0bb;\"| '''[[Pope Adrian IV|Adrian IV]]''', '''''[